    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require phone providers to stop charging for handsets on expiration of contract",
        "additional_details": "In October 2017 Citizens Advice found that three of the four largest mobile phone providers \u2013 Vodafone, EE and Three \u2013 continued to charge customers extra for a handset after it had been paid off as part of their fixed deal.  The majority of people who are caught out by this are the over 65s.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/about-us/how-citizens-advice-works/media/press-releases/mobile-phone-networks-overcharging-loyal-customers-by-up-to-38-a-month/ ",
        "background": "The government should make it law that mobile phone providers should be obliged to make sure that any customers staying in a contract past the end of a fixed deal have their monthly bill reduced to reflect the cost of the handset.",
